{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"81380a61-e9a7-4447-95b9-2b3d4e2bb044","content":"No files found in the working directory. I'll provide the solution directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` to enable compiled bindings:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"32\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**1. Enable strict compiled bindings** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors -->\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**2. What this gives you:** With `x:DataType` declared, the XAML compiler resolves bindings at compile time. If you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), you get a **build error** like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\n**3. Opting out for dynamic bindings** — if a specific binding must remain uncompiled (e.g., binding to a dynamically-typed context), use:\n\n```xml\n<Label Text=\"{Binding Path=SomeDynamic, x:DataType=x:Object}\" />\n```\n\nor set `x:DataType` to an empty string on a child element to disable it locally.\n\n**Key points:**\n- `x:DataType` must reference the actual ViewModel type (not an interface, unless that's what you bind against).\n- Compiled bindings are faster at runtime (no reflection) and safer at build time.\n- Ensure the `xmlns:vm` namespace matches your ViewModel's actual CLR namespace.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1a50cb48-2f2a-4d7c-a655-e70561ffe8d5","outputTokens":656,"requestId":"9434:1EB0D5:1471E79:16D25F4:6A066F83"},"id":"732577fa-26b8-43d0-be58-8b82e97961b3","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:57:53.704Z","parentId":"1aeb615b-a07a-4d73-aca0-68fabe008f4d"}
